11.5.8 Phase 5 — Prior sensitivity
The Nash model has a single Dirichlet prior. A power-scaling check verifies that the posterior over \(\theta\) is driven by the data, not by the \(\text{Dirichlet}(2,2,2)\) prior. With 300 trials per player each action occurs \(\approx 100\) times, providing strong information relative to the weak prior concentration. We expect the posterior to be largely prior-insensitive across a wide range of power-scaling factors.


